Chatgpt 5.5 result

Security analysis result
I analyzed both uploaded files statically and did not execute them.
Overall verdict: I did not find clear static evidence of a backdoor or malware implant in the firmware image. The main risk is that this package contains a powerful firmware-flashing utility plus a full Intel SPI/IFWI firmware image. If used incorrectly or if the firmware image is not from the exact trusted OEM release chain, it could brick the system, overwrite identifiers, weaken firmware protections, or install persistent firmware-level changes.
Intel’s own community discussion confirms FPT is distributed as part of CSME packages, and independent firmware documentation describes Intel FPT as a tool for internal SPI flash programming on Intel PCH systems; that matches the strings and capabilities found inside Fpt.efi.  
