What I would verify on the real machine before trusting it
Run hardware/firmware checks with tools such as CHIPSEC, Intel MEInfo, OEM tools, or BIOS setup:
Secure Boot enabled
PK / KEK / db / dbx present
Intel Boot Guard Verified Boot enabled
Intel Boot Guard Measured Boot enabled
Flash Descriptor locked
BIOS_CNTL.BLE enabled
BIOS_CNTL.SMM_BWP enabled
Protected Range registers configured
ME/CSME manufacturing mode closed
BIOS Lock enabled
No service-mode / flash-override jumper active
Without those runtime checks, static analysis cannot prove the platform is protected.
